What you need to know:

The English champions had not even scored in their last four league games, but their front three sparked back into life as Roberto Firmino ended a 492-minute goalless drought in first-half stoppage time.Kane had soldiered on after twice receiving treatment on ankle knocks in the first-half and was eventually replaced at the break.Trent Alexander-Arnold doubled Liverpool's lead before Pierre-Emile Hojbjerg immediately pulled a goal back for Spurs early in the second-half.Sadio Mane secured a badly-needed win for Jurgen Klopp's men 25 minutes from time.